\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 """\
FTSE Follow the Green Scanner\
==============================\
A Streamlit web app for UK long-term investors using Felix's\
"Follow the Money" / "Follow the Green" methodology.\
\
Run with:\
    streamlit run app.py\
\
Install dependencies:\
    pip install streamlit yfinance pandas plotly\
\
Felix's Core Philosophy:\
    "Big institutional money (funds, pension schemes, market makers) can't\
     hide their activity \'97 they move too many shares. Their buying and selling\
     leaves unmistakable footprints in the volume data. Our job is simply to\
     read those footprints and follow the smart money."\
\
Key Rules Explained in Code Below:\
    1. SMA50  \uc0\u8594  Defines whether we're in an uptrend or downtrend\
    2. Volume Spike (>1.5\'d7) \uc0\u8594  Detects institutional activity\
    3. Rising Volume Trend \uc0\u8594  Confirms sustained accumulation, not a one-off\
    4. Price > SMA50 + Volume Spike + Rising Vol = BULLISH ACCUMULATION\
    5. Price < SMA50 + Volume Spike = BEARISH DISTRIBUTION (danger zone)\
"""\
\
